MODIFICATIONS

This derivative work includes the following significant modifications
and enhancements to the original Infinite-ISP:

1. HDR Pipeline Support:
   - Decompanding (PWC) module for companded sensor data
   - Tone mapping before or after demosaic
   - Multiple tone mapping operators (Durand, ACES, Hable, Reinhard)
   - HDR bit depth support (up to 24-bit)

2. Advanced Demosaic Algorithms:
   - Hamilton-Adams demosaic implementation
   - PPG (Patterned Pixel Grouping) demosaic
   - VNG (Variable Number of Gradients) optimized version
   - LMMSE (Least Mean Square Error) demosaic
   - AHD (Adaptive Homogeneity-Directed) demosaic

3. Gamma Correction Pipeline Fix:
   - Corrected gamma position in pipeline for standards compliance
   - Proper linear RGB processing in color space conversion
   - 16-bit to 8-bit linear conversion before CSC
   - Standards-compliant with ITU-R BT.601/709 and IEC 61966-2-1

4. Lens Shading Correction:
   - Radial polynomial vignetting correction

5. Optional GPU Acceleration:
   - CuPy-based GPU implementations for performance

6. Enhanced Debugging and Visualization:
   - Histogram plotting and dynamic range estimation
   - Tone mapping curve visualization
   - Enhanced logging system

7. Documentation:
   - Extensive implementation documentation
   - Algorithm reference guides
   - Quick reference documents

